  "original_title": "\u0dc1\u0dca\u200d\u0dbb\u0dd3 \u0dbd\u0d82\u0d9a\u0dcf\u0dc0: \u0da2\u0db1\u0db4\u0dad\u0dd2 \u0d85\u0dc3\u0dd4\u0db1 \u0dc3\u0db3\u0dc4\u0dcf \u0dc0\u0db1 \u0dad\u0dbb\u0d9c\u0dba \u0dc3\u0dd4\u0dc5\u0dd4 \u0db8\u0ddc\u0dc4\u0ddc\u0dad\u0d9a\u0dd2\u0db1\u0dca",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "Sri Lanka: The race for the presidential seat in a few moments",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "Parliamentarians of Sri Lanka are scheduled to vote for a new president today due to former President Gotabhaya Rajapaksa fleeing the country and resigning amid public protests held due to the country's economic crisis.",
        "Acting President Ranil Wickremesinghe, nominated by the ruling party for that role, is considered to be the leading candidate in this race.",
        "But the protesters want to see Wickremesinghe also resign.",
        "Wickramasinghe faces a serious challenge from Dallas Alahapperuma, a member of the ruling party who has the support of the main opposition.",
        "Whoever is elected by Parliament will be tasked with serving the remainder of Gotabaya's term, which ends in November 2024.",
        "Currently, Sri Lanka is a bankrupt state and is facing acute shortages of food, fuel and other basic supplies.",
        "The country needs a stable government in order to start new negotiations with the International Monetary Fund (IMF) to recover the country from the crisis.",
        "225 Members of Parliament have qualified to vote today (July 20). The candidate who gets more than half of the votes wins the contest.",
        "It is a three-way contest between Wickramasinghe, Alahaperuma, and National People's Power leader Anura Kumara Dissanayake."
      ],
